00:16:25.590 --> 00:16:27.760
Now, once you're
at a big incumbent,

00:16:27.760 --> 00:16:31.390
if you work for one
of the big places,

00:16:31.390 --> 00:16:35.010
you'll feel that little bit
more constraint, a little bit

00:16:35.010 --> 00:16:36.630
more compliance officers.

00:16:36.630 --> 00:16:39.360
You're more lawyered, you
have more accountants.

00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:41.560
But you should still
have the same values.

00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:43.560
I say this sincerely.

00:16:43.560 --> 00:16:45.690
Don't break the law.

00:16:45.690 --> 00:16:47.370
No, no, sincerely.

00:16:47.370 --> 00:16:49.360
But when you're at a
startup, you tend--

00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:51.810
there's always some ambiguity,
and you take a little bit

00:16:51.810 --> 00:16:54.940
more reputational risk.

00:16:54.940 --> 00:16:57.690
You tend to.

00:16:57.690 --> 00:16:59.790
So there's a bunch
of incumbents that

00:16:59.790 --> 00:17:03.360
are trying to get in the Chicago
Mercantile Exchange, Eurex,

00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:05.760
Intercontinental Exchange,
which owns the New York Stock

00:17:05.760 --> 00:17:06.260
Exchange.

00:17:06.260 --> 00:17:09.930
We'll do a whole class
on what they're doing

00:17:09.930 --> 00:17:12.900
there later in the semester.

00:17:12.900 --> 00:17:15.210
Fidelity, that's spending
significant amount

00:17:15.210 --> 00:17:19.310
of money looking
at it and others.

00:17:19.310 --> 00:17:21.450
So the framework that
we've talked about,

00:17:21.450 --> 00:17:24.329
about guarding against
illicit activity, stability,

00:17:24.329 --> 00:17:26.220
and the investing public--

00:17:26.220 --> 00:17:28.230
I'm going to sort
through each of these,

00:17:28.230 --> 00:17:29.700
but it's tax compliance.

00:17:29.700 --> 00:17:34.810
No government wants to
shrink their tax base.

00:17:34.810 --> 00:17:38.410
Now, some governments
want to attract activity

00:17:38.410 --> 00:17:43.010
that shrinks the other
jurisdiction's tax base,

00:17:43.010 --> 00:17:47.150
but it's not about shrinking
your own tax base usually.

00:17:47.150 --> 00:17:50.090
I mean, you might
by law lower taxes,

00:17:50.090 --> 00:17:53.090
but you're not
really looking to--

00:17:53.090 --> 00:17:54.530
generally,
governments don't want

00:17:54.530 --> 00:17:57.890
to promote whatever the
definition of illicit activity.

00:17:57.890 --> 00:17:59.840
We don't need to define
that in this class.

00:17:59.840 --> 00:18:03.570
It's a normative thing that
happens culture by culture,

00:18:03.570 --> 00:18:05.750
jurisdiction by jurisdiction.

00:18:05.750 --> 00:18:10.010
But there tends to be
something that's prohibited--

00:18:10.010 --> 00:18:14.330
drug running, for instance,
child trafficking.

00:18:14.330 --> 00:18:16.640
I mean, there are certain
things that are broadly

00:18:16.640 --> 00:18:18.200
defined as illicit,
and then there's

00:18:18.200 --> 00:18:23.180
some that changes depending
upon the culture and the society

00:18:23.180 --> 00:18:25.730
and the times we're living in.

00:18:25.730 --> 00:18:28.940
Terrorism financing, clearly.

00:18:28.940 --> 00:18:32.440
And then sanctions, it's
a tool of foreign policy

00:18:32.440 --> 00:18:35.180
that countries like our own,
but Europe and elsewhere

00:18:35.180 --> 00:18:37.560
often use sanctions to try to--

00:18:37.560 --> 00:18:39.320
it's centuries old.

00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:43.670
It's called blockades in an
earlier century with the ships.

00:18:43.670 --> 00:18:46.010
But now, we do it
more electronically

00:18:46.010 --> 00:18:48.170
and commercially.

00:18:48.170 --> 00:18:52.520
Financial stability tends
to be about the stability

00:18:52.520 --> 00:18:56.780
of the overall economy
or the Fiat currency.

00:18:56.780 --> 00:18:59.630
Or I put a little
second picture there,

00:18:59.630 --> 00:19:02.780
the stability of the
commercial banking system.

00:19:02.780 --> 00:19:05.990
So financial stability can
mean a lot of different things,

00:19:05.990 --> 00:19:09.620
but it's usually about
the currency, the economy,

00:19:09.620 --> 00:19:14.690
or the central bank system
and commercial bank system.

00:19:14.690 --> 00:19:17.660
But to some countries,
not a majority,

00:19:17.660 --> 00:19:19.280
some countries'
financial stability

00:19:19.280 --> 00:19:21.590
is about capital controls.

00:19:21.590 --> 00:19:25.970
If a country is controlling
somewhere the valuation

00:19:25.970 --> 00:19:27.740
of their Fiat
currency-- remember,

00:19:27.740 --> 00:19:30.320
we talked a lot about money.

00:19:30.320 --> 00:19:33.230
But if some don't
want to flood and they

00:19:33.230 --> 00:19:36.410
want to control the value
of their Fiat currency,

00:19:36.410 --> 00:19:39.260
then they often have
capital controls.

00:19:39.260 --> 00:19:44.240
And for those countries, this
whole world of crypto finance

00:19:44.240 --> 00:19:45.680
touches on that.

00:19:45.680 --> 00:19:49.070
And then the investing
public, the consuming public,

00:19:49.070 --> 00:19:51.470
we'll talk about investor
protection and consumer

00:19:51.470 --> 00:19:54.660
protection are not
exactly the same.

00:19:54.660 --> 00:19:57.830
The two words market
integrity means basically

00:19:57.830 --> 00:20:01.820
we promote economic activity
if you can have confidence

00:20:01.820 --> 00:20:04.740
in central market structures.

00:20:04.740 --> 00:20:07.700
Whether that's the
pricing of apples

00:20:07.700 --> 00:20:11.380
or the pricing of
Apple stock, it's

00:20:11.380 --> 00:20:14.020
in essence that there's
not fraud and manipulation

00:20:14.020 --> 00:20:15.960
in that market.

00:20:15.960 --> 00:20:18.090
And the more
transparent the prices

00:20:18.090 --> 00:20:22.140
are both before you do a
transaction and after--

00:20:22.140 --> 00:20:23.745
what's called
pre-trade transparency

00:20:23.745 --> 00:20:28.140
and post-trade transparency--
the more transparent

00:20:28.140 --> 00:20:31.490
and the more you can root
out manipulation and fraud,

00:20:31.490 --> 00:20:32.680
there's more integrity.

00:20:32.680 --> 00:20:37.000
Usually very simply-- and this
is a lot of economic study goes

00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:37.810
into it--

00:20:37.810 --> 00:20:40.990
you lower the risk
premium in that market.

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:44.050
In essence, you can have more
confidence in that market.

00:20:44.050 --> 00:20:46.180
And secondly, you
have more competition

00:20:46.180 --> 00:20:48.780
in the price discovery function.

