00:39:40.140 --> 00:39:43.870
Anybody want to tell me what
the Bank Secrecy Act is?

00:39:43.870 --> 00:39:46.030
Is it Nicholas?

00:39:46.030 --> 00:39:49.763
See, I can read your name
there and see how that worked.

00:39:49.763 --> 00:39:51.180
AUDIENCE: I'm not
sure what it is.

00:39:51.180 --> 00:39:52.638
GARY GENSLER: OK,
that's all right.

00:39:52.638 --> 00:39:56.490
Bank Secrecy Act was passed
a few decades ago so probably

00:39:56.490 --> 00:39:58.320
before most of us in this room--

00:39:58.320 --> 00:40:00.870
after I was born, but
most of you were born.

00:40:00.870 --> 00:40:05.370
Anybody want to say what
the Bank Secrecy Act is?

00:40:05.370 --> 00:40:06.060
Daniel?

00:40:06.060 --> 00:40:09.020
AUDIENCE: Is it the Bank Secrecy
Act that deals with KYC and AML

00:40:09.020 --> 00:40:10.610
and essentially
knowing the parties

00:40:10.610 --> 00:40:11.920
that you're interacting with?

00:40:11.920 --> 00:40:12.570
GARY GENSLER: Correct.

00:40:12.570 --> 00:40:13.195
That's correct.

00:40:13.195 --> 00:40:17.220
It's really trying to protect
against secret transactions

00:40:17.220 --> 00:40:20.640
or what's often called
money laundering.

00:40:20.640 --> 00:40:22.740
And behind the money
laundering laws

00:40:22.740 --> 00:40:25.290
is knowing who the
customer is of a bank.

00:40:25.290 --> 00:40:29.750
So you'll hear these letters,
KYC, know your customer;

00:40:29.750 --> 00:40:33.430
AML, anti-money laundering.

00:40:33.430 --> 00:40:35.710
And the Bank Secrecy
Act, underneath it then,

00:40:35.710 --> 00:40:38.110
has reporting
obligations that anyone

00:40:38.110 --> 00:40:41.350
who has to report under
the Bank Secrecy Act

00:40:41.350 --> 00:40:45.040
has to report when there's
large transactions.

00:40:45.040 --> 00:40:49.060
If you go into the bank and
you ask them, can you please--

00:40:49.060 --> 00:40:54.190
I want to take a withdraw
of $11,000 of US currency.

00:40:54.190 --> 00:40:56.560
They have to fill out
a report, because I

00:40:56.560 --> 00:40:59.470
believe the triggers $10,000.

00:40:59.470 --> 00:41:03.630
You walk in and you
get $500, no report.

00:41:03.630 --> 00:41:06.960
But there's various
suspicious activity reporting

00:41:06.960 --> 00:41:09.510
and other large
transaction reporting

00:41:09.510 --> 00:41:12.085
that gets triggered in
the US Bank Secrecy Act.

00:41:12.085 --> 00:41:13.710
But you will hear
over and over again--

00:41:13.710 --> 00:41:16.830
even if you never invest or
work in a blockchain company,

00:41:16.830 --> 00:41:20.100
you will hear something
called KYC and AML.

00:41:20.100 --> 00:41:25.920
And it's these two
regimes that kind of work.

00:41:25.920 --> 00:41:29.430
They're not the best,
but they do their job

00:41:29.430 --> 00:41:32.470
to give the official sector
and the banking sector

00:41:32.470 --> 00:41:36.430
a sense of who owns the
accounts and when there's

00:41:36.430 --> 00:41:40.300
suspicious activity that
there's a reporting obligation

00:41:40.300 --> 00:41:41.890
into the authorities.

